Lab-6
02/09/2022

Q1. WAP to swap private data member of two classes. [The classes have no relation with each other].

Q2. Create two classes which stores distance in feet, inches and meter, centimeter format respectively.
Write a function which compares distance in object of these classes and displays the larger one.

Q3. Create a class which stores time in hh:mm format. Include all the constructors. The parameterized
constructor should initialize the minute value to zero, if it is not provided.

Q4. Create a class which stores a string and its length as data members. Include all the constructors.
Include a member function to join two strings and display the concatenated string.

Q5. WAP to calculate simple interest of given principal amount. 
(Take rate of interest as default argument)